reviews.text: Product received was as described except it had been previously opened and (2) of the (10) switches had been previously installed and were damaged. Mounting screws were missing on (2) of the (10). One of the two had a scratch across the face. The other had damage to the ground strap on the mount where the screw makes contact for grounding the box. Unfortunately, I had not opened the box until I was ready to install the switches, only to discover the above and the return window had closed. Not happy at all with Amazon on this purchase. The undamaged product works just fine. Would by the product again, likely not from Amazon. Although they switches are listed as residential grade, they are actually marked Specification Grade and are rated for 120-277Vac.

reviews.productTitle: Leviton 5601-2WM 15 Amp, 120/277 Volt, Decora Rocker Single-Pole AC Quiet Switch, Residential Grade, Grounding, 10-Pack, White
reviews.text: I tested out several switches in stores, because the clicking sound when turning most switches on and off was much too loud for my liking. This 5601, in particular was disappointing, since it is promoted as a quiet switch. It's not, at least to my ear! The video posted in the review here by Stuart Schwartz on 6/30/20 really shows this. What if you are like me and know that every time you flip this switch you will regret buying it due to the loud clicking noise? There is a solution, the Leviton 5621. This switch is as close to quiet as you can imagine! It is more expensive since it is made to handle up to 20 amps of power, vs 15 amps with this model. A 20 amp switch will work fine in a 15 amp circuit. You are just paying for a more beefy switch than you need. Not a problem. In addition, the 5621 does NOT have the company name "Leviton" in raised letters on the switch. Many recent 5061 reviews mention this undesirable feature. So, while the 5621 is significantly more expensive, at least you have the option if you desire a near quiet switch without the company name in raised letters on the switch.
reviews.date: Reviewed in the United States on July 30, 2020
reviews.title: Not a true quiet switch. The Leviton 5621, is MUCH more quiet. (Comparison 5601 vs 5621)

reviews.productTitle: Leviton 5601-2WM 15 Amp, 120/277 Volt, Decora Rocker Single-Pole AC Quiet Switch, Residential Grade, Grounding, 10-Pack, White
reviews.text: I don't understand why they bothered to add "quiet switch" to the title, these certainly are not. The click it makes is actually kinda annoying and probably wouldn't have even bothered me if quiet wasn't in the title. I had specific expectations of a silent experience turning on and off all the switches in my home but the only thing these things are quieter than is perhaps yelling at Alexa to turn on the light for me.
